reviews.review: Overall, I think it did a wonderful job of fan service for the final installment and getting to where J.J. wanted it to be in the end. I wasn't a huge fan of The Last Jedi, but I did enjoy this movie.

My expectations were honestly so low for this film after the last jedi and the official reviews. How wrong I was - this was everything I wanted from a star wars film. It's a shame that some of the plot had to be rushed through, particularly at the start, but this is more the last Jedi's failure than anything. Can't wait to see it again! I'll just have to leave an awkward Episode 8 shaped hole in my collection...

Such a good way to tie up loose ends and finish out the saga. A couple questionable components, but still felt very Star Wars to me and if you don't nitpick about small details, then it's a great movie!!
Throw the Jedi lore in the trash. In my personal opinion it's a bit boring and underwhelming. I wish that they could have has an "endgame" moment with all the Jedi ghosts. ðŸ˜•

I came in the theater with little to no expectations for Rise of Skywalker, but I was completely blown away. There was never a dull moment, and all the moments with Carrie Fisher were very touching. I can see why some people may not like it, but in my humble opinion this was a fantastic way to end the Skywalker saga.

The problem is the whole trilogy had no direction or overarching story. This movie tries to make up for that by being 3 movies in 1, and in doing so has a break-neck speed with no pauses for character development and gaping plot holes.
